According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Algal Extract for Cosmetics market was valued at USD 0.52 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 0.57 billion in 2026 to USD 1.05 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 8.9% during the forecast period. The market is being fueled by the growing popularity of natural cosmetics, vegan formulations, and advancements in algae extraction technologies that enhance ingredient efficacy and commercial scalability.
